HEADWORD: Innavigable
<hw>In*nav"i*ga*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>innavigabilis</ets> : cf. F. <ets>innavigable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Navigable</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being
navigated; impassable by ships or vessels.</def> <au>Drygen.</au> --
